description.narrative: Project development objective: To support rural communities and producer organizations in increasing (i) the production of selectedcrops and livestock species in selected areas of the Recipient's territory; and (ii) the use of sustainable land and watermanagement practices in climate vulnerable ecosystems.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section 1.A.3 | Description :The Recipient shall establish staff and thereafter maintain, at alltimes during the implementation of the Project, a regional coordination unit in each of the Targeted Regions, with mandate,staffing and other resources satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :10-Jan-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I.E.1 | Description :The Recipient shall: (a) prepare under terms of reference acceptable tothe Association, a resettlement policy framework for the Project; (b) afford the Association a reasonable time to exchange viewswith the Recipient on said framework; and (c) thereafter, adopt and disclose such resettlement policy framework as shall have beenapproved by the Association. | Due Date :31-Dec-2012

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section II.B.4 | Description :The Recipient shall recruit (a) the external auditor referred to inSection 4.09 (b) of the General Conditions in accordance with Section III of Schedule 2 of this Agreement and pursuant to terms ofreference satisfactory to the Association; and (b) an internal auditor, whose qualifications and experience and terms of referenceshall be acceptable to the Association. | Due Date :31-Jan-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section II.B.5 | Description :The Recipient shall acquire, install and thereafter maintain accountingsoftware acceptable to the Association, for the Project. | Due Date :31-Dec-2012
